<i>adjective</i>: 밝다 [박따], 깍듯하다 [깍뜨타다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adjective</i><br>
<dt>밝다 [박따]</dt><br>
<dd>1. light; brilliant; luminous</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 물체가 내는 빛이 환하다.</dd><br>
<dd>The light emanating from something being bright.</dd><br>
<dd>2. bright</dd><br>
<dd>빛을 많이 받아 어떤 장소가 환하다.</dd><br>
<dd>A place being light as a result of getting a lot of sun.</dd><br>
<dd>3. light</dd><br>
<dd>색깔이 어둡거나 탁하지 않다.</dd><br>
<dd>A color being not dark or impure.</dd><br>
<dd>4. keen; sharp</dd><br>
<dd>시력이나 청력이 좋다.</dd><br>
<dd>Eyesight or hearing being good.</dd><br>
<dd>5. courteous; well-behaved</dd><br>
<dd>예절이 바르다.</dd><br>
<dd>Polite.</dd><br>
<dd>6. clean</dd><br>
<dd>건전하고 바르다.</dd><br>
<dd>Sound and fair.</dd><br>
<dd>7. cheerful; bright</dd><br>
<dd>표정, 성격, 분위기 등이 유쾌하고 활발하다.</dd><br>
<dd>A facial expression, personality, mood, etc., being lively and pleasant.</dd><br>
<dd>8. good at; clever</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 잘 알아 확실하게 처리하는 면이 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>Knowing well about something and dealing with it perfectly.</dd><br>
<dd>9. bright; promising</dd><br>
<dd>예측되는 미래가 긍정적이다.</dd><br>
<dd>One's expected future being positive.</dd><br>
<dd>10. well acquainted with; familiar with</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일에 대하여 아는 것이 많다.</dd><br>
<dd>Knowing a lot about something.</dd><br>
<dt>깍듯하다 [깍뜨타다]</dt><br>
<dd>polite; courteous; well-mannered</dd><br>
<dd>매우 예의가 바르다.</dd><br>
<dd>Being very polite in manners.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>